    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-08-11T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-08-11T14:00:00-05:00" n="214"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/1579: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Arica</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Von Tresckow</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-08-11T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 11, 1925—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department much disturbed by press reports regarding restrictions placed by
                    Chilean authorities on movement of Peruvians in Tacna and Arica and that these
                    restrictions have even been applied to Peruvian officials connected with the
                    Plebiscitary and Boundary Commissions.<note n="48" xml:id="d214fn48">The first
                        meeting of the Plebiscitary Commission was held on August 5, 1925.</note>
                    Please telegraph immediately substance of all restrictive measures as well as
                    full details of Ordoñez incident.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
